'''Taṣnhajit n Srayr''' tga zzɣ twja n tutlayin timaziɣin n ugafa. Ar si-s sawaln iẓnagn izdɣn ɣ ugzzum agmuḍan n arrif amɣrab (Kutama)<ref>"[[ethnologue:SJS|Senhaja Berber]]". Ethnologue. Retrieved 2020-10-12.</ref>.

Tga tulayt-ad zzɣ twja n tulayin n waṭlas<ref>Lameen Souag, 2004: "Senhaja de Srair is not Zenati, but rather Atlas, belonging (despite location) with Middle Atlas Tamazight."</ref>. tṛḍl-d mnnwt tɣawsiwin zɣ tutlayt taddjart-nns, [[Tutlayt Tarifit|Tarifit]].

== Tintlayin ==
Tintlayin n Tsnhajit gant tid: Bni Aḥmd, Bni Bcir, Bni bnsar, Bni Jnnus, Bni Meswi, Bni Seddat, Kutama, Sarkat d Tagsut.

